---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCapture from '../components/EmailCapture.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About AnimeBulk — The Anime Fitness Platform"
  description="AnimeBulk bridges anime culture and real-world fitness science. Learn about our mission, our approach, and why we build character-inspired workout programs."
>
  <div class="pt-16">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="bg-dark-800 border-b border-white/5 py-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <p class="text-brand-400 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Our Story</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-display tracking-wide text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          We Train Like <span class="text-gradient">Anime Characters.</span><br />
          For Real.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          AnimeBulk was born from a simple frustration: the best fitness inspiration in the world lives inside anime, but the actual training programs were scattered, unscientific, and built by people who'd never touched a barbell.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Mission -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-20">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-display tracking-wide text-white mb-4">The Problem We Solve</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Anime fans are some of the most motivated people in the world when it comes to fitness. They watch Goku train in 100× gravity. They see Tanjiro run up mountains. They feel the fire when Naruto refuses to give up.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            But when they search "how to train like Goku" or "Tanjiro workout routine," they find generic programs slapped with anime names — no real connection to the character's physique, fighting style, or training philosophy.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
            AnimeBulk fixes that. Every program we build is researched from the source material, grounded in exercise science, and designed to actually produce the physique and capabilities of the character.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-dark-700 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            {[
              { icon: '🎯', title: 'Character-Accurate', desc: 'Programs built around each character\'s actual physique, fighting style, and training arc.' },
              { icon: '🧬', title: 'Science-Backed', desc: 'Progressive overload, periodization, and evidence-based nutrition — not bro-science.' },
              { icon: '📈', title: 'Results-Focused', desc: 'Every program has measurable benchmarks so you know exactly how you\'re progressing.' },
            ].map(item => (
              <div class="flex gap-4">
                <span class="text-2xl flex-shrink-0">{item.icon}</span>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-1">{item.title}</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Values -->
      <div class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-display tracking-wide text-white mb-10 text-center">
          What We <span class="text-gradient">Believe</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          {[
            {
              number: '01',
              title: 'Passion is the best pre-workout',
              desc: 'When you train like a character you love, you show up harder, push further, and stay consistent longer. Identity-based fitness works.',
            },
            {
              number: '02',
              title: 'Science doesn\'t care about aesthetics',
              desc: 'Progressive overload, protein synthesis, and recovery are the same whether you\'re inspired by Goku or a generic fitness influencer. We use the science.',
            },
            {
              number: '03',
              title: 'Anyone can start',
              desc: 'Naruto was dead last in his class. Tanjiro was a charcoal seller. Rock Lee had no natural talent. Every character starts from zero. So can you.',
            },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="bg-dark-700 border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-brand-500/20 transition-colors">
              <div class="text-4xl font-display text-brand-500/30 mb-3">{item.number}</div>
              <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- How programs are built -->
      <div class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-display tracking-wide text-white mb-6">
          How We Build <span class="text-gradient">Programs</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-2xl">
          Every AnimeBulk program goes through the same research process before a single exercise is written.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            { step: '1', title: 'Character Research', desc: 'We analyze the character\'s physique, fighting style, training arc, and any canon information about their training methods.' },
            { step: '2', title: 'Physique Mapping', desc: 'We identify the key physical qualities that define the character — relative strength, explosiveness, endurance, muscle mass distribution.' },
            { step: '3', title: 'Exercise Selection', desc: 'We select exercises that develop those specific qualities using evidence-based exercise science.' },
            { step: '4', title: 'Program Design', desc: 'We structure the program with proper periodization, progressive overload, and recovery built in.' },
            { step: '5', title: 'Nutrition Integration', desc: 'We add a nutrition framework calibrated to the program\'s demands and the character\'s physique goals.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex gap-4 p-5 bg-dark-700/50 border border-white/5 rounded-xl hover:border-brand-500/20 transition-colors">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-brand-500/20 border border-brand-500/30 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-brand-400 font-bold text-sm">
                {item.step}
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-1">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-display tracking-wide text-white mb-4">Ready to Start?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-8">Pick your character and begin your transformation.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/workouts" class="btn-primary text-lg px-8 py-4">Browse All Workouts</a>
          <a href="/blog" class="btn-secondary text-lg px-8 py-4">Read the Blog</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Email Capture -->
    <EmailCapture />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
